  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The purpose of the grant is to provide support to Women&apos;s Rights Center Poland (WRC) in its effort to intensify strategic litigation related to gender-based violence and discrimination and promote improvement of relevant laws. A particular focus in case selection will be on domestic abuse involving rape or murder. Among the legislative goals of WRC are challenging the current legal definition of rape, and to introduce restraining orders. Monitoring of state action plans addressing domestic violence meaningfully with allocated budget will be a priority. Finally, WRC aims to strengthen its regional impact through taking a lead in campaigning for a new EU directive on violence against women, and promote a binding EU directive on this issue</narrative>
  </description>
